
[1]mediocrity

   MEDIOC'RITY, n. [L.mediocritas, from mediocris, middling;
   medius,middle.]

   1. A middle state or degree; a moderate degree or rate. A mediocrity of
   condition is most favorable to morals and happiness. A mediocrity of
   talents well employed will generally ensure respectability.

   Men of age seldom drive business home to the full period, but content
   themselves with a mediocrity of success.

   2. Moderation; temperance.

   We owe obedience to the law of reason, which teacheth mediocrity in
   meats and drinks.
